link refer : https://getgrav.org/blog/macos-ventura-apache-mysql-vhost-apc
MySQL
1. Install mysql
  brew update
  brew install mariadb
2. After a successful installation, you can start the server ane ensure it autostarts in the future with:
  brew services start mariadb
3.You must change MySQL server password and secure your installation. The simplest way to do this is to use the provided script:
  sudo /opt/homebrew/bin/mysql_secure_installation
II change sphp 8.0 to the version you want to install xdebug for (8.0+)
    sphp 8.0
    pecl uninstall -r xdebug
    pecl install xdebug
 Xdebug Configuration
You will now need to remove the zend_extension="xdebug.so" entry that PECL adds to the top of your php.ini. So edit this file and remove the top line. In this example we will use 7.2 but it's the same procedure for each version of PHP.
code /opt/homebrew/etc/php/7.2/php.ini
Once that line is removed, we can add a new file with a proper entry to the recently bulit xdebug.so library:
[xdebug]
zend_extension="xdebug.so"
xdebug.mode=debug
=====================
[xdebug]
zend_extension="xdebug.so"
xdebug.remote_enable=1
xdebug.remote_host=localhost
xdebug.remote_handler=dbgp
xdebug.remote_port=9000
  
  
